When implementing any email that is sent automatically (newsletter, reminders, order lifecycle, marketing automations), always use the Email Control Center system:

- Add/maintain a template in Supabase `public.email_templates` (via a migration) with a stable `template_key`.
- Render it via `lib/email/renderTemplate.ts` and include `{{brand_header}}` + `{{social_footer}}` from `lib/email/socialFooter.ts`.
- Persist every outgoing message in Supabase `public.email_outbox` (insert draft/scheduled) and send via `lib/email/sendOutboxEmail.ts` (`sendOutboxViaResend`) so status + provider id are recorded.
- Avoid sending “one-off” hardcoded HTML emails directly via Resend unless it is an admin-only operational alert.

If a new template needs new variables, ensure admin preview mocks include them:
- `app/api/admin/emails/preview/route.ts`
- `app/api/admin/emails/test-send/route.ts`

